==English==

===Noun===
'''brand''' ([[brands]])

#A marker for cattle, a hot iron.
#(Advertising) a name, symbol, logo, or other item used to distinguish a product or manufacturer from its competitors.
#:'''''Brands''' of breakfast cereal.''
#(Advertising) the intangible sum of a product's attributes: its name, packaging, and price, its history, its ''reputation'', and the way it's advertised. – credit David Ogilvy.

